  "description" : "[h1]Project FR: Core Engine - The Ultimate French Localization for Starbound[/h1]\n\n[b]Project FR: Core Engine[/b] is not just a translation pack; it is a complete, modern reconstruction of the French localization for Starbound. Rebuilt from the ground up by a single developer, this high-performance engine replaces obsolete methods to provide a seamless and 100% integrated experience.\n\n[h2]✨ Features:[/h2]\n[list]\n[*] [b]100% Vanilla Coverage:[/b] Over 4,000 items, objects, quests, dialogues, and UI elements from the base game are fully translated.\n[*] [b]Dynamic Localization Engine:[/b] Optimized JSON dictionary system that reduces CPU load and prevents the crashes common in older translation mods.\n[*] [b]Smart Persistence:[/b] Translations are injected directly into item parameters. If you uninstall the mod, items already in your inventory stay in French!\n[*] [b]Built for the Future:[/b] This \"Core\" acts as a foundation for upcoming translation modules for major mods (Frackin' Universe, Shellguard, etc.).\n[/list]\n\n[h2]🛠️ Why switch to Project FR?[/h2]\nWith the previous French translation mod officially abandoned since July 2024, it was time to provide the community with a tool up to 2026 standards. [b]Project FR[/b] cleans up the files, fixes historical typos, and ensures perfect compatibility with current game versions.\n\n[h2]📥 Installation:[/h2]\n1. Click [b]Subscribe[/b].\n2. Launch Starbound.\n3. Enjoy the game entirely in French!\n[i](No complex setup required; the Core Engine handles everything at startup).[/i]\n\n[h2]🐞 Bug Reports & Missing Strings:[/h2]\nWith over 4,000 entries, a typo might still slip through. If you find untranslated text or encounter a bug:\n[list]\n[*] Post a message in the [b]Discussions[/b] tab.\n[*] Attach your [b]starbound.log[/b] via pastebin if necessary.\n[/list]\n\n[h2]🚧 Work in Progress (Inspections Beta):[/h2]\nYou may notice that some [b]inspection texts[/b] (when using the magnifying glass on objects) are still in English.\n[list]\n[*] [b]Why?[/b] I am currently developing a [b]Lua injection method[/b] to translate these strings dynamically instead of overwriting thousands of individual files. This ensures better compatibility with other mods.\n[*] [b]Updates:[/b] These strings will be localized instantly in upcoming Core Engine updates.\n[/list]\n\n[hr][/hr]\n\n[h3]📜 Credits & Acknowledgments:[/h3]\n[i]The engine, scripts, and dictionaries were entirely rebuilt by myself.[/i] \nHowever, to maintain visual consistency and honor 10 years of French modding, I would like to thank the original [b]Starbound FR[/b] team (Yohann Catherine, Mickael30HG, Pho3niX, Shyning, LoGeek, Phaenix, Canarder) for their visual assets and the foundation they laid.\n\n[b]License:[/b] Released under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. (See included LICENSE file).",
